quran[71]{c,v,t}:
  80,1,He frowned and turned away
  80,2,that the blind man came to him
  80,3,And what should teach thee? Perchance he would cleanse him
  80,4,"or yet remember, and the Reminder profit him"
  80,5,But the self-sufficient
  80,6,to him thou attendest
  80,7,"though it is not thy concern, if he does not cleanse himself"
  80,8,And he who comes to thee eagerly
  80,9,and fearfully
  80,10,to him thou payest no heed
  80,11,No indeed; it is a Reminder
  80,12,"and whoso wills, shall remember it"
  80,13,upon pages high-honoured
  80,14,"uplifted, purified"
  80,15,by the hands of scribes
  80,16,"noble, pious"
  80,17,Perish Man! How unthankful he is
  80,18,Of what did He create him
  80,19,"Of a sperm-drop He created him, and determined him"
  80,20,then the way eased for him
  80,21,"then makes him to die, and buries him"
  80,22,"then, when He wills, He raises him"
  80,23,No indeed! Man has not accomplished His bidding
  80,24,Let Man consider his nourishment
  80,25,We poured out the rains abundantly
  80,26,then We split the earth in fissures
  80,27,and therein made the grains to grow
  80,28,"and vines, and reeds"
  80,29,"and olives, and palms"
  80,30,and dense-tree'd gardens
  80,31,"and fruits, and pastures"
  80,32,an enjoyment for you and your flocks
  80,33,And when the Blast shall sound
  80,34,upon the day when a man shall flee from his brother
  80,35,"his mother, his father"
  80,36,"his consort, his sons"
  80,37,every man that day shall have business to suffice him
  80,38,Some faces on that day shall shine
  80,39,"laughing, joyous"
  80,40,some faces on that day shall be dusty
  80,41,o'erspread with darkness
  80,42,"those -- they are the unbelievers, the libertines"
  81,1,When the sun shall be darkened
  81,2,when the stars shall be thrown down
  81,3,when the mountains shall be set moving
  81,4,when the pregnant camels shall be neglected
  81,5,when the savage beasts shall be mustered
  81,6,when the seas shall be set boiling
  81,7,when the souls shall be coupled
  81,8,when the buried infant shall be asked
  81,9,for what sin she was slain
  81,10,when the scrolls shall be unrolled
  81,11,when heaven shall be stripped off
  81,12,when Hell shall be set blazing
  81,13,when Paradise shall be brought nigh
  81,14,then shall a soul know what it has produced
  81,15,No! I swear by the slinkers
  81,16,"the runners, the sinkers"
  81,17,by the night swarming
  81,18,by the dawn sighing
  81,19,truly this is the word of a noble Messenger
  81,20,"having power, with the Lord of the Throne secure"
  81,21,"obeyed, moreover trusty"
  81,22,Your companion is not possessed
  81,23,he truly saw him on the clear horizon
  81,24,he is not niggardly of the Unseen
  81,25,And it is not the word of an accursed Satan
  81,26,where then are you going
  81,27,It is naught but a Reminder unto all beings
  81,28,for whosoever of you who would go straight
  81,29,"but will you shall not, unless God wills, the Lord of all Being"